title.narrative: Capacity of child protection actors to prevent and respond to cases of violence against children strengthened at national anddecentralised level and access of children and families to child protection services, increased.

description.narrative: With UNICEF assistance, civil registration became a priority for MoJ and its CP partners. 61,613 children were registered with UNICEF support and five (5) additional BR services were established in health facilities. Capacities of social service workforce, frontline workers, psychologist, teachers, health professionals, and CSOs, were enhanced to improve CP preventive and responsive services, as well as data gathering and reporting. 484 children who experienced violence were reached by CP services. GBV, FGM and child marriage prevention in schools and communities mobilized 103,024 people. Sixty-three (63) communities declared the abandonment of FGM and other forms of violence against children. | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:24/01/2022
